      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is a growing consensus among forward-thinking urban planners that congestion pricing is a vital component of achieving aggressive climate and air quality goals. By putting a price on driving during peak hours, it directly incentivizes the shift towards public transit, cycling, or remote work. This mechanism is seen as an effective, market-based lever to reduce fossil fuel consumption in city centers. Therefore, it is increasingly viewed not just as a traffic fix, but as necessary climate infrastructure.",
      "source": "target",
