      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Planners who advocate for congestion pricing acknowledge the equity concerns, which is why they insist on robust mitigation strategies. These strategies typically involve using the generated revenue to fund transit improvements and provide rebates or exemptions for low-income drivers. The goal is to ensure the policy is progressive, meaning the revenue benefits the community, rather than simply acting as a revenue stream for the city. Ultimately, the fairness rests on how effectively these revenue-recycling mechanisms are designed and implemented.",
      "source": "target",
